}{\plain \fs24 \f1 \tab }{\plain \fs24 \b\f1 82-93.}{\plain \fs24 \f1   Publius Papinius Statius (45-96) was born in Naples and not in Toulouse, \softline
birthplace of a different Statius, a rhetorician; Dante's error was a common one (perhaps deriving \softline
from the glosses by Lactantius [ca. 300] to the poems of Statius) and he helped propagate it, since \softline
